OpenAI and Anthropic Hello World Vignette
==========================================

Description:
    Demonstrates basic usage of the OpenAI and Anthropic Python client
    libraries. Each section follows the same pattern: instantiate a client
    using an API key from the environment, send a simple chat message, and
    print the response. Serves as a minimal working template for building
    more complex LLM-powered applications.

    OpenAI section:
        - Model: gpt-4o-mini (replaces deprecated gpt-3.5-turbo)
        - Client: openai.OpenAI()
        - API: client.chat.completions.create()

    Anthropic section:
        - Model: claude-sonnet-4-5
        - Client: anthropic.Anthropic()
        - API: client.messages.create()

Prerequisites:
    Environment variables set in ~/.zshrc:
        export OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-proj-..."
        export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="sk-ant-..."

References:
    1. OpenAI Python library
       https://platform.openai.com/docs/overview
    2. Anthropic Python library
       https://docs.anthropic.com/en/api/getting-started

Revision History:
    2024-07-18  Original development
                - OpenAI hello world using openai.chat.completions.create()
                - Documented API key setup process

    2025-04-01  Compatibility review and updates for Python 3.14 / macOS M5
                - Updated to modern OpenAI client pattern: OpenAI()
                - Updated model: gpt-3.5-turbo -> gpt-4o-mini
                  (gpt-3.5-turbo deprecated by OpenAI in late 2024)
                - Added print() for completion response content
                - Added Anthropic Claude hello world section
                  using claude-sonnet-4-5
"""






# Install if needed (run once in terminal, not here):
# pip install openai anthropic

# Check environ vars
import os
print(os.environ.get('OPENAI_API_KEY', 'NOT FOUND'))
print(os.environ.get('ANTHROPIC_API_KEY', 'NOT FOUND'))


import os                         # To read environment variables
from openai import OpenAI         # Modern OpenAI client (v1.0+)
import anthropic                  # Anthropic Claude client



import openai
import anthropic as anth
print(f'OpenAI version:    {openai.__version__}')
print(f'Anthropic version: {anth.__version__}')






# Instantiate the OpenAI client — reads OPENAI_API_KEY from environment
openai_client = OpenAI(api_key=os.environ['OPENAI_API_KEY'])






completion = openai_client.chat.completions.create(
    # https://platform.openai.com/docs/models
    model='gpt-4o-mini',          # gpt-3.5-turbo deprecated late 2024
    messages=[
        {
            'role': 'user',
            'content': 'Hello, world! What happened on a day like today in history?',
        },
    ],
)

# Print the response content
print(completion.choices[0].message.content)









# Instantiate the Anthropic client — reads ANTHROPIC_API_KEY from environment
anthropic_client = anthropic.Anthropic(api_key=os.environ['ANTHROPIC_API_KEY'])






from datetime import date
today = date.today().strftime("%B %d")

message = anthropic_client.messages.create(
    model='claude-sonnet-4-5',
    max_tokens=1024,
    messages=[
        {
            'role': 'user',
            'content': f'Hello, world! Today is {today}. What happened on this day in history?',
        },
    ],
)
print(message.content[0].text)



